The catalysts in Everett''s tales are surprising: a stuffed boar''s head, mounted on the wall of a diner, becomes an object of intense, inexplicable desire; a painter is driven to the point of suicide by a mute who returns day after day to mow the artist''s lawn; the loss of a pair of dentures sparks a turn toward revelation.', NULL, NULL, '1555972381', NULL, 246, NULL, NULL, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/8545209-L.jpg', '/works/OL8386911W', NULL, '1996', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'big-picture-percival-l-everett', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 07:16:48', '2026-03-24 23:24:42');
